<script type="application/ld+json">{JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What drives property values in Kelvin Grove Brisbane?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Kelvin Grove's character home market and modern apartment sector trade at quite different price points. Heritage cottages and renovated Queenslanders in the upper parts of the suburb attract strong competition from buyers who have specifically chosen the suburb for its character and CBD proximity. Apartments in the Kelvin Grove Urban Village range widely by size, floor level and building vintage. Contact Daniel for a current appraisal on your specific property." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "How long does it take to sell a home in Kelvin Grove?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Well-presented character homes in Kelvin Grove typically sell within 25 to 40 days when priced on recent comparable evidence. The urban village apartment market is more varied, tracking 30 to 55 days depending on the building, floor plan and amenity offering." } },
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the lifestyle like in Kelvin Grove Brisbane?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Kelvin Grove offers a rare combination of inner-city proximity and genuine neighbourhood character. Victoria Park sits to the south, connecting the suburb to the CBD precinct on foot or by bike. The QUT Creative Industries campus brings a consistent energy to the area, and the urban village precinct has created a walkable hub that older parts of the suburb lacked. It is an area that functions well for people who want to live close to the city without the density of apartment-only precincts." } },
